label: b Thank you Miss Nana as a member of the diaspora who has lived longer in LN now in the UK than in Indonesia I don t miss news about Indonesia including the presidential candidate debate br Well first of all I m not a supporter of candidate pair 2 But I m a professional candidate As an Engineer for the most technologically advanced large items on the face of the earth I want to give my opinion here regarding the purchase of used PSWT ships goods by the Minister of Defense br 1 It is possible that Indonesia wants to buy new aircraft the latest technology and will not be given permission by developed countries Indonesia is a third country the weapons or aircraft in circulation have rules who can buy them or not br Purchasing new weapons is a matter of transferring the latest technology so each country has its own rules for exporting technology It could be that Indonesia is not qualified even though there is money to buy it br But I don t think it s possible for Pak Prabowo to say that our country is not qualified As a good statesman we must maintain the country s self respect br But the reality is that I work in the field like that br 2 Used goods don t mean bad In fact it might even be possible to save money depending on the destination for example just buying a plane As an engineer I really don t like new aircraft new types factory output I prefer aircraft that have a track record performance history That s a cheaper price and safer if the same goal can be achieved why not buy used as long as Indonesia knows how to maintain changing parts etc I don t think it s a problem br br Once again this is just my opinion br Good health to all of you br May Indonesia be peaceful prosperous just and victorious br

was related to the ratio of 9 3 times the increase in salaries housing for TNI soldiers between during the SBY Jokowi era In fact Prabowo s answer can immediately be broken especially the explanation regarding refocusing the budget priority scale in the disbursement plan procurement plan during the Covid 19 period at the direction of President c q Minister of Finance as State General Treasurer br br The substance of Prabowo s answer above actually also answers the question asked by Presidential Candidate Ganjar Pranowo regarding the realization of the Minimum Essential Forces MEF achievement which was only 65 49 percent even though the target was 79 percent which was actually also hampered by the budget allocation in terms of handling Covid 19 for the past 2 5 years br br Similarly regarding Anies insinuation about the purchase of used aircraft by the Ministry of Defense which can also be explained simply and substantively by Prabowo that the operationalization of purchasing new aircraft is only to meet the MEF target In fact it will only be ready for at least 3 years and can only be used for at least the next 7 years Therefore in the context of efficiency and utilization of the available budget aircraft were acquired which although not newly produced were still young max 15 years of use br br Other substantive problems that must be understood thoroughly First in depth regarding the achievements of the MEF as Ganjar asked Prabowo at least it must be based on the use of 4 four variables br Main weapons system equipment alutsista br Maintenance and upkeep of defense equipment br Facilities and defense infrastructure as well as br Professionalism and welfare of soldiers br br However so far MEF achievements have only been calculated using the defense equipment variable while the other three variables have not been assessed because the calculation formula is more complicated br br This is what is substantially Prabowo repeatedly conveyed both to Ganjar and Anies that the MEF issue could not be explained in a short debate session like this considering that all data reports and calculation formulations had been presented holistically before Commission I of the DPR RI br br And unfortunately if the secret and strategic defense intelligence calculation data is explained in detail in an open forum such as last night s presidential debate then the risk of other countries identifying our country s military strength becomes very high apart from diplomatically and geopolitics could disrupt bilateral relations with several countries that have previously carried out defense cooperation with Indonesia such as regarding the production of defense equipment and other weapons Therefore if you look closely so far the RDP Hearing Meeting between Commission I DPR RI and the Minister of Defense is more often held behind closed doors It is this substance that Prabowo seems to be very guarded about confidentially br br The last substantial discussion that was touched on in tonight s debate was related to KSS South South Cooperation This issue is actually a continuation of the idea of development cooperation between developing countries which began with the Asia Africa Conference KAA in Bandung in 1955 This conference is actually considered a historical milestone for the formation of South South Cooperation KSS Bung Karno then called it the first inter continental conference of colored peoples in human history br br In short SSC is a cooperation scheme between developing countries carried out through various mutual bilateral and multilateral relationships to produce joint solutions for development Southern countries br br Regarding the SSC issue Prabowo must honestly admit that he understands better the historical dimensions and substance of how Indonesia must position itself geopolitically Descriptively Prabowo said that Indonesia had succeeded in becoming an example for countries in the Southern world in terms of successful domestic resource governance such as downstreaming etc br br So many countries in Africa are now looking at us coming to us learning from us because we are considered a successful southern country such as low inflation still growth good trade balance five year trade surplus consecutively said Prabowo It is through this perspective of independence and sovereignty that Prabowo actually wants to illustrate that the solidarity of the SSC countries as a continuation of the new KAA will be realized So it has nothing to do with strengthening ASEAN as stated by Anies and responded to by Ganjar br br How can Indonesia s geo political bargaining position be to embrace southern countries if Indonesia s economy is still colonized and not yet independent it seems like a developing country that still poor So Anies historical conclusion which refers to Ali Sastroamidjojo s diplomatic dimension that Indonesia must spread embracing politics as a SSC road map can immediately be broken by Prabowo by stating that in state leadership we want to lead and be a role model for south south countries right You can just talk nonsense but you have to be an example first strengthening the domestic economy then you
